{"title_page": "Abdul Razak Alhassan", "text_new": "{{short description|Ghanaian mixed martial arts fighter}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Abdul Razak Alhassan\n| other_names     = Judo Thunder<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2016/11/16/13653786/welcome-to-the-ufc-ward-alhassan|title=UFC Belfast gets last minute WW fight|first=Zane|last=Simon|date=16 November 2016|publisher=Bloody Elbow|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref>\n| image           = \n| image_size      =\n| alt             = \n| caption         =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1985|8|11}}\n| birth_place     = [[Accra]], [[Ghana]]\n| death_date      = \n| death_place     =\n| death_cause     =\n| residence       = \n| nationality     = [[Ghanaian]]\n| height          = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}\n| weight          = {{convert|170|lb|kg st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Welterweight (MMA)|Welterweight]] <br>[[Middleweight (MMA)|Middleweight]]\n| reach           = 73 in\n| style           = [[Judo]], [[Muay Thai]]<ref name=UFCprofile>{{cite web|url=http://www.ufc.com/fighter/Abdul-Razak-Alhassan|title=Abdul Razak Alhassan - Official UFC Profile|publisher=UFC.com|accessdate=September 18, 2018}}</ref>\n| stance          = \n| fighting_out_of = [[Fort Worth, Texas]], United States\n| team            = \n| rank            = Black belt in [[Judo]]<ref name=UFCprofile />\n| wrestling       = \n| university      = \n| school          = \n| years_active    = 2013-present\n| mma_kowin       = 10\n| mma_subwin      = \n| mma_decwin      = \n| mma_dqwin       = \n| mma_koloss      = \n| mma_subloss     = \n| mma_decloss     = 1\n| mma_draw        = \n| mma_nc          = \n| url             =\n| sherdog         = 151701\n| footnotes       =\n| updated         =\n}}\n\n'''Abdul Razak Alhassan''' (born August 11, 1985) is a [[Ghanaian]] [[mixed martial arts|mixed martial artist]] who competes in the [[Welterweight (MMA)|welterweight]] division of the [[Ultimate Fighting Championships|UFC]]. A professional since 2013, he formerly fought in [[Bellator MMA|Bellator]] and [[Legacy Fighting Championship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/05/the-accidental-assassin-abdul-razak-alhassan-on-his-reluctant-path-to-ufc-fight-night-109|title=The accidental assassin: Abdul Razak Alhassan on his reluctant path to UFC Fight Night 109|date=25 May 2017|publisher=|accessdate=31 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2014/3/7/5479980/bellator-111-results-dantas-vs-leone|title=Bellator 111 results: Dantas ve. Leone|first=Shaun|last=Al-Shatti|date=7 March 2014|publisher=|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2015/9/25/9400077/bellator-143-results-and-highlights-warren-beats-davis-grove-tko-beltran-mma-news|title=Bellator 143: Warren wins snoozer, Grove gets TKO|first=Mookie|last=Alexander|date=25 September 2015|publisher=|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/11/ufc-fight-night-99-results-abdul-razak-alhassan-drops-charlie-ward-in-53-second-slugfest|title=UFC Fight Night 99 results: Abdul Razak Alhassan drops Charlie Ward in 53-second slugfest|date=19 November 2016|publisher=|accessdate=7 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Mixed martial arts career==\n===Early career===\nAfter training and competing in [[judo]] for 22 years and earning his black belt, Alhassan transitioned to [[mixed martial arts]]. He made his professional debut in 2013, winning via TKO in just 25 seconds. Alhassan then compiled an overall record of 6-0 before being signed by the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship|UFC]].\n\n===Ultimate Fighting Championship===\nAlhassan made his promotional debut at [[UFC Fight Night: Mousasi vs. Hall 2]] against [[Charlie Ward (fighter)|Charlie Ward]] on November 19, 2016. He won via knockout 53 seconds into the first round and was awarded a ''Performance of the Night'' bonus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2016/11/ufc-fight-night-99-results-abdul-razak-alhassan-drops-charlie-ward-in-53-second-slugfest|title=UFC Fight Night 99 results: Abdul Razak Alhassan drops Charlie Ward in 53-second slugfest|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Dann Stupp|date=2016-11-19|accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/UFC-Fight-Night-99-Bonuses-Marshman-Lee-Ledet-Alhassan-Collect-3650K-113849|title=UFC Fight Night 99 bonuses: Marshman, Lee, Ledet, Alhassan collect $50K|publisher=sherdog.com|author=Tristen Critchfield|date=2016-11-19|accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>\n\nAlhassan then lost a split decision to [[Omari Akhmedov]] at [[UFC Fight Night: Gustafsson vs. Teixeira]] on May 28, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/05/ufc-fight-night-109-results-omari-akhmedov-hands-abdul-razak-alhassan-first-loss|title=UFC Fight Night 109 results: Omari Akhmedov hands Abdul Razak Alhassan first loss|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Ben Fowlkes|date=2017-05-28|accessdate=2017-05-28}}</ref>\n\nAlhassan faced [[Sabah Homasi]] on December 2, 2017, at [[UFC 218]], winning by TKO in the first round; some felt referee Herb Dean had stopped the fight prematurely.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/12/ufc-218-results-abdul-razak-alhassan-tko-sabah-homasi-first-protests-of-stoppage|title=UFC 218 results: Abdul Razak Alhassan TKOs Sabah Homasi in first, despite wide protests of stoppage|date=2017-12-03|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2017-12-03|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nDue to the controversial stoppage in the first fight, a rematch with Homasi was held on January 20, 2018, at [[UFC 220]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2017/12/abdul-razak-alhassan-vs-sabah-homasi-shifted-to-ufc-220|title=Abdul Razak Alhassan vs. Sabah Homasi shifted to UFC 220|date=2017-12-14|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2017-12-15|language=en-US}}</ref> Alhassan indisputably knocked him out in the first round.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/01/ufc-220-results-abdul-razak-alhassan-leaves-no-doubt-in-rematch-with-sabah-homasi|title=UFC 220 results: Abdul Razak Alhassan leaves no doubt in rematch with Sabah Homasi|date=2018-01-21|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref> The win earned him the [[List of UFC bonus award recipients|Performance of the Night]] bonus<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2018/01/ufc-220-bonuses-daniel-cormier-abdul-razak-alhassan-among-50000-winners|title=UFC 220 bonuses: Daniel Cormier, Abdul Razak Alhassan among $50,000 winners|date=2018-01-21|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-01-21|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nAlhassan was expected to face [[Muslim Salikhov]] on April 14, 2018, at [[UFC on Fox 29]].<ref name=\"twomore\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/sports/mma/2018/02/14/matt-lopez-vs-alejandro-perez-added-ufc-fox-29-gila-river-arena/338542002/|title=Matt Lopez vs. Alejandro Perez added to UFC on Fox 29 at Gila River Arena|publisher=azcentral.com|author=Greg Moore|date=2018-02-15|accessdate=2018-02-15}}</ref> He was replaced by [[Ricky Rainey]] due to injury.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sherdog.com/news/news/Ricky-Rainey-Replaces-Abdul-Razak-Alhassan-Meets-Muslim-Salikhov-at-UFC-on-Fox-29-134357|title=Ricky Rainey Replaces Abdul Razak Alhassan, Meets Muslim Salikhov at UFC on Fox 29|last=Sherdog.com|website=Sherdog|access-date=2018-03-31}}</ref>\n\nAlhassan knocked out [[Niko Price]] in 43 seconds on September 8, 2018, at [[UFC 228]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/09/ufc-228-results-abdul-razak-alhassan-blasts-niko-price-in-just-43-seconds|title=UFC 228 results: Abdul Razak Alhassan blasts Niko Price in just 43 seconds|date=2018-09-09|work=MMAjunkie|access-date=2018-09-09|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Championships and awards==\n* '''[[Ultimate Fighting Championship]]'''\n** [[List of UFC bonus award recipients|Performance of the night]] (Two times)\n\n==Mixed martial arts record==\n<!-- ALL THE HIDDEN SPANS ARE FOR PROPER TABLE SORTING. PLEASE DO NOT EDIT THEM UNLESS